From 87ea08616c7a59ba49cf730ff635340d4deca7f3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 11:01:51 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Production readiness fixes: patch critical CVE, edge-runtime
 bundling bug, rate limiting, security headers, N+1 query
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Upgrade Next.js 14.2.18 -> 14.2.35 (patches CVE-2025-29927, a middleware
  auth-bypass vulnerability that directly undermined this app's route
  gating) and next-auth to the latest compatible beta.
- Split auth config into auth.config.ts (edge-safe, no providers) and
  auth.ts (full config with bcrypt) so middleware.ts no longer bundles
  Node-only APIs into the Edge Runtime — was a real build warning,
  shrank the middleware bundle 105kB -> 79kB.
- Add security headers (X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options,
  Referrer-Policy, Strict-Transport-Security, Permissions-Policy).
- Add per-email rate limiting on login (10 attempts/15min) — unit-verified.
- Add Prisma directUrl so migrations work correctly against a pooled
  production connection (Supabase/PgBouncer transaction mode).
- Batch the diagnostic-tab heatmap into one API call instead of 8
  per-domain round-trips (new /api/dashboard/heatmap endpoint).
